verbs.description: unpersonify (third-person singular simple present unpersonifies, present participle unpersonifying, simple past and past participle unpersonified)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To undo the personification of; to remove the personhood of.
examples: […]  with a life-destroying, hideous article clumsily stuck before the personified noun to unpersonify it, to make masculine what should be feminine,  […]
